  "size": 4541,
  "founded": 1769,
  "description": "Dartmouth College is a private Ivy League research university in Hanover, NH, founded in 1769 under a charter signed by colonial New Hampshire governor John Wentworth. One of the nine colonial colleges established before the American Revolution, it pairs an undergraduate liberal-arts core with the Thayer School of Engineering, Tuck School of Business, Geisel School of Medicine, and the Guarini School of Graduate and Advanced Studies. Set on a wooded campus around the historic Dartmouth Green, it is among the smallest and most selective national research universities.",
